01:30:31,767 --> 01:30:34,887
I promised to spare you that
but you must help me.

770
01:30:37,022 --> 01:30:38,682
I'm out of my depth.

771
01:30:41,986 --> 01:30:43,266
Come on, Anne.

772
01:30:51,871 --> 01:30:53,578
Drink this, now!

773
01:30:59,252 --> 01:31:01,922
That's it.
Good.

774
01:31:05,092 --> 01:31:06,372
Well, swallow it!

775
01:31:37,916 --> 01:31:39,244
Please, forgive me.

776
01:31:41,335 --> 01:31:42,414
I'm sorry.

777
01:32:56,743 --> 01:32:58,237
- Who's there?
- It's me.

778
01:32:58,578 --> 01:33:00,238
- Eva?
- Yes.

779
01:33:02,582 --> 01:33:04,076
Just a minute.

780
01:33:56,219 --> 01:33:57,879
- Hello.
- Hello.

781
01:33:59,555 --> 01:34:00,718
What was going on?

782
01:34:01,224 --> 01:34:03,133
Nothing.
I was in the toilet.

783
01:34:04,852 --> 01:34:06,181
No, come in.

784
01:34:17,573 --> 01:34:21,072
- Why this unannounced visit?
- What's going on with mum?

785
01:34:21,535 --> 01:34:24,702
Nothing.
What should be going on?

786
01:34:28,250 --> 01:34:30,077
Don't you want to sit down first?

787
01:34:37,300 --> 01:34:38,759
Why are you in Paris?

788
01:34:38,927 --> 01:34:42,759
What's going on with mum?
Why don't you answer the phone?

789
01:34:43,640 --> 01:34:46,348
Since our last conversation, I left
four messages on your answering machine.

790
01:34:46,557 --> 01:34:48,454
Why don't you call back?

791
01:34:49,187 --> 01:34:52,105
Sorry. I didn't listen to it.
Forgive me.

792
01:34:52,232 --> 01:34:54,521
Don't you realize we're worried?

793
01:34:56,694 --> 01:34:59,102
Your worries are no use to me.

794
01:34:59,656 --> 01:35:03,784
No, don't get me wrong.
I'm not criticizing you.

795
01:35:04,953 --> 01:35:07,954
I just don't have the time
to deal with your worries, that's all.

796
01:35:08,081 --> 01:35:11,580
- Dad...
- No, let's stop this conversation.

797
01:35:12,752 --> 01:35:16,881
Your mother is just as could have been
expected: bad the whole time.

798
01:35:18,300 --> 01:35:22,047
She is turning more and more
into a helpless child.

799
01:35:22,511 --> 01:35:25,548
It's sad and humiliating
for her and for me.

800
01:35:25,681 --> 01:35:28,433
And she doesn't want
to be seen in that state.

801
01:35:28,559 --> 01:35:32,509
Even the last time
she did not want you to come.

802
01:35:33,189 --> 01:35:34,786
You two have your own life.
Nothing wrong with that.

803
01:35:34,995 --> 01:35:36,993
But let us have our life too.
Okay?

804
01:35:37,318 --> 01:35:39,560
Dad, what's the matter?

805
01:35:40,405 --> 01:35:43,690
Nothing.
Your visit caught me by surprise.

806
01:35:43,867 --> 01:35:48,693
And I'm annoyed that you show up here
to check that everything's okay.

807
01:35:49,288 --> 01:35:51,530
Who do you think you are?

808
01:35:57,254 --> 01:35:59,413
Stay here, please.

809
01:36:02,218 --> 01:36:03,416
Please!

810
01:36:15,063 --> 01:36:16,059
Mum?

811
01:36:20,193 --> 01:36:21,142
Mum!

812
01:36:30,079 --> 01:36:31,870
Tell me, what's going on?
Have you gone crazy?

813
01:36:31,997 --> 01:36:32,697
Sit down.

814
01:36:32,831 --> 01:36:35,618
I don't want to sit down.
What's going on here?

815
01:36:35,750 --> 01:36:39,499
Nothing's going on. I want to spare
us all a pointless drama.

816
01:36:40,130 --> 01:36:43,084
I presume your mother is asleep.
She sleeps all day.

817
01:36:43,550 --> 01:36:45,922
And then she wakes up at night.

818
01:36:47,262 --> 01:36:49,800
If you really want to,
we'll go and see her in a little while.

819
01:36:51,183 --> 01:36:52,677
Now, sit down.

820
01:37:06,781 --> 01:37:12,642
We do our speech exercises every day,
or we sing together.

821
01:37:14,497 --> 01:37:19,788
Usually I wake up around 5.
At that time, she's still awake.

822
01:37:20,295 --> 01:37:25,170
We change the nappy,
I rub cream on her to avoid bed sores.

823
01:37:26,258 --> 01:37:31,335
Then, around 7, I try to persuade her
to eat and drink.

824
01:37:32,723 --> 01:37:35,049
Sometimes it works, sometimes not.

825
01:37:35,559 --> 01:37:38,763
Sometimes she tells me things
from her childhood.

826
01:37:38,938 --> 01:37:41,476
Or calls for help for hours.

827
01:37:42,942 --> 01:37:46,275
Then, suddenly, she starts giggling.

828
01:37:47,487 --> 01:37:48,982
Or crying.

829
01:37:53,035 --> 01:37:55,905
Nothing of any of that
is worth showing.

830
01:38:00,542 --> 01:38:03,034
You can't forbid me
from seeing her.

831
01:38:06,340 --> 01:38:07,205
No.

832
01:39:10,319 --> 01:39:11,695
It's me, Mum.

833
01:39:27,169 --> 01:39:29,494
Can I do something for you?

834
01:39:40,182 --> 01:39:41,297
Mum.

835
01:39:42,977 --> 01:39:44,305
Mum.

836
01:39:44,854 --> 01:39:46,265
Mum.

837
01:39:49,274 --> 01:39:50,437
Mum.

838
01:40:58,885 --> 01:41:00,000
The tea isn't very hot any more.

839
01:41:04,473 --> 01:41:05,967
But it does make you feel better.

840
01:41:17,862 --> 01:41:18,893
Thanks.

841
01:41:34,378 --> 01:41:37,047
It was silly of me
to lock the door.

842
01:41:37,506 --> 01:41:38,751
I'm sorry.

843
01:41:39,425 --> 01:41:41,133
You took me by surprise.

844
01:41:43,304 --> 01:41:44,798
I'm sorry.

845
01:41:46,557 --> 01:41:48,016
What's going to happen now?

846
01:41:50,310 --> 01:41:51,804
What's going to happen now?

847
01:41:53,480 --> 01:41:57,228
The nurse comes
three times a week.

848
01:41:57,359 --> 01:42:00,941
Every two weeks Dr. Bertier
and the hairdresser come.

849
01:42:01,738 --> 01:42:04,063
That's what you wanted to know?
No?

850
01:42:06,368 --> 01:42:09,203
Things will go on
as they have done up until now.

851
01:42:10,789 --> 01:42:12,126
They'll go from bad to worse.

852
01:42:12,334 --> 01:42:14,521
Things will go on,
and then one day it will all be over.

853
01:42:16,627 --> 01:42:18,585
You can't go on like this, Dad.

854
01:42:18,713 --> 01:42:19,911
- No?
- No.

855
01:42:20,882 --> 01:42:22,459
What do you suggest?

856
01:42:23,176 --> 01:42:25,334
Can't we have a serious talk,
you and me?

857
01:42:26,304 --> 01:42:28,973
What do you call "a serious talk"?

858
01:42:30,016 --> 01:42:32,258
Do you want to have Mom live with you?

859
01:42:33,019 --> 01:42:35,193
Do you want to pack her off
to a care home?

860
01:42:35,402 --> 01:42:37,233
Is this what you want?

861
01:42:38,691 --> 01:42:42,190
Go on, talk to me seriously!

862
01:42:46,490 --> 01:42:48,234
All long...

863
01:42:49,452 --> 01:42:51,076
Ding dong...

864
01:42:54,832 --> 01:42:57,454
Yes, it swung to and fro.

865
01:42:57,585 --> 01:43:00,788
Yes, yes, to, fro.

866
01:43:01,089 --> 01:43:02,167
You...

867
01:43:03,882 --> 01:43:05,460
Very serious...

868
01:43:05,676 --> 01:43:06,956
Like that.

869
01:43:07,261 --> 01:43:08,292
Yes.

870
01:43:09,346 --> 01:43:10,425
Like that.

871
01:43:12,057 --> 01:43:13,172
Serious.

872
01:43:14,184 --> 01:43:16,343
Yes, I was very uptight.

873
01:43:16,812 --> 01:43:18,093
Yes.

874
01:43:19,190 --> 01:43:20,684
Up...tight.

875
01:43:25,154 --> 01:43:29,898
It... was... nice.

876
01:43:46,884 --> 01:43:48,461
Hurts.

877
01:43:52,430 --> 01:43:54,257
Hurts.

878
01:43:57,965 --> 01:43:58,820
Hurts.

879
01:44:11,116 --> 01:44:14,319
What's the matter.
Where do you hurt?

880
01:44:19,540 --> 01:44:20,951
What's going on?

881
01:44:21,959 --> 01:44:23,288
Is it the nappy?

882
01:44:24,086 --> 01:44:25,367
Is it full?

883
01:44:28,549 --> 01:44:29,960
Where do you hurt?

884
01:44:36,266 --> 01:44:40,179
It's all right, it's all right.
I'm here.

885
01:44:44,690 --> 01:44:45,970
Everything's fine.

886
01:44:50,696 --> 01:44:51,941
We will...

887
01:44:53,199 --> 01:44:55,524
Do you want me
to tell you a story?

888
01:44:57,787 --> 01:45:00,871
But you must be quiet,
I can't talk too loud.

889
01:45:02,375 --> 01:45:03,998
It wears me out.

890
01:45:08,296 --> 01:45:10,455
When I was little,

891
01:45:10,882 --> 01:45:13,883
well, I wasn't as little as all that,

892
01:45:14,344 --> 01:45:19,220
I think it was
toward the end of primary school,

893
01:45:19,558 --> 01:45:21,883
so I was about 10.

894
01:45:23,854 --> 01:45:27,852
Dad and mum had sent me
to a holiday camp.

895
01:45:28,274 --> 01:45:33,150
They thought it would do me good to
spend the summer with kids my own age.

896
01:45:34,531 --> 01:45:37,448
We were lodged in an old castle

897
01:45:40,161 --> 01:45:43,365
in the midst of the forest.
I think it was in the Auvergne.

898
01:45:44,458 --> 01:45:45,916
I don't remember.

899
01:45:46,835 --> 01:45:51,082
In any case it was the opposite
of what I'd expected.

900
01:45:54,342 --> 01:45:58,885
We had to get up at 6 in the morning
and plunge into a lake.

901
01:45:59,222 --> 01:46:02,342
It was a small lake
not far from the castle.

902
01:46:02,600 --> 01:46:06,680
It was fed by an icy mountain stream.

903
01:46:07,605 --> 01:46:11,437
We had to enter it running,
in a double file.

904
01:46:13,570 --> 01:46:16,605
You know,
I was never very sporty.

905
01:46:18,115 --> 01:46:25,432
They had worked out a programme
to keep us on the go all day,

906
01:46:27,750 --> 01:46:34,369
Probably to nip in... in the bud

907
01:46:35,049 --> 01:46:38,086
any potential pubescent impulses.

908
01:46:39,053 --> 01:46:41,211
But the worst thing was the food.

909
01:46:43,098 --> 01:46:49,183
The third day after our arrival,
there was rice pudding for lunch.

910
01:46:49,480 --> 01:46:51,389
I hate rice pudding.

911
01:46:51,982 --> 01:46:58,186
We sat at long tables in a huge hall.

912
01:46:58,697 --> 01:47:00,939
I didn't want to eat the stuff.

913
01:47:03,869 --> 01:47:07,033
One of the monitors said to me:

914
01:47:07,737 --> 01:47:11,996
"If you don't clear your plate,
you won't get out of here."

915
01:47:13,879 --> 01:47:17,212
So after the meal everybody left,

916
01:47:17,716 --> 01:47:20,883
and I remained alone, in tears.

917
01:47:23,680 --> 01:47:27,725
I had made a secret pact with mum.

918
01:47:28,185 --> 01:47:33,605
I was to write to her every week.
I was to send her a postcard.

919
01:47:33,856 --> 01:47:39,729
If I liked the stay,
I was to draw flowers,

920
01:47:40,280 --> 01:47:42,735
if not, stars.

921
01:47:43,742 --> 01:47:49,080
She kept the card.
It was covered all over in stars.

922
01:47:51,458 --> 01:47:55,205
After three hours,
I was finally allowed to get out.

923
01:47:56,837 --> 01:48:00,503
I went up to my room,
got into bed

924
01:48:01,342 --> 01:48:03,667
I had a fever of over 40 degrees.

925
01:48:04,428 --> 01:48:05,923
It was diphtheria.

926
01:48:07,140 --> 01:48:11,967
I was taken
to the nearest hospital

927
01:48:12,478 --> 01:48:14,685
and sent to quarantine.

928
01:48:15,523 --> 01:48:18,772
Which meant that mum,
when she came to visit me,

929
01:48:19,443 --> 01:48:22,693
could only wave at me
through a window.

930
01:48:27,952 --> 01:48:30,359
At some point I lost that postcard.

931
01:48:32,414 --> 01:48:33,743
It's a pity.

932
01:59:29,603 --> 01:59:32,806
... you won't believe it.
A pigeon came in,

933
01:59:32,940 --> 01:59:36,356
for the second time already,
through the light well.

934
01:59:36,485 --> 01:59:40,897
This time I caught it.
In fact it wasn't difficult at all.

935
01:59:41,030 --> 01:59:43,356
But I set it free again.

936
02:01:38,814 --> 02:01:40,522
I'm almost done.

937
02:01:44,819 --> 02:01:46,812
You can put your shoes on if you want.

938
02:02:56,515 --> 02:02:57,713
Thank you.

939
02:03:05,649 --> 02:03:07,476
Aren't you taking a coat?